106 CDriver::CDriver(char* confFile, unsigned short val_nZone, SU2_Comm MPICommunicator, bool dummy_geo) :
107 CDriverBase(confFile, val_nZone, MPICommunicator), StopCalc(false), fsi(false), fem_solver(false), dry_run(dummy_geo) {
108 
109  /*--- Start timer to track preprocessing for benchmarking. ---*/
110 
111  StartTime = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
112 
113  /*--- Initialize containers with null --- */
114 
115  InitializeContainers();
116 
117  /*--- Preprocessing of the config files. ---*/
118 
119  PreprocessInput(config_container, driver_config);
120 
121  /*--- Retrieve dimension from mesh file ---*/
122 
123  nDim = CConfig::GetnDim(config_container[ZONE_0]->GetMesh_FileName(),
124  config_container[ZONE_0]->GetMesh_FileFormat());
125 
126  /*--- Output preprocessing ---*/
127 
128  PreprocessOutput(config_container, driver_config, output_container, driver_output);
129 
130 
131  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
132 
133  /*--- Read the number of instances for each zone ---*/
134 
135  nInst[iZone] = config_container[iZone]->GetnTimeInstances();
136 
137  geometry_container[iZone] = new CGeometry** [nInst[iZone]] ();
138  iteration_container[iZone] = new CIteration* [nInst[iZone]] ();
139  solver_container[iZone] = new CSolver*** [nInst[iZone]] ();
140  integration_container[iZone] = new CIntegration** [nInst[iZone]] ();
141  numerics_container[iZone] = new CNumerics**** [nInst[iZone]] ();
142  grid_movement[iZone] = new CVolumetricMovement* [nInst[iZone]] ();
143 
144  /*--- Allocate transfer and interpolation container --- */
145 
146  interface_container[iZone] = new CInterface*[nZone] ();
147  interpolator_container[iZone].resize(nZone);
148 
149  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++) {
150 
151  config_container[iZone]->SetiInst(iInst);
152 
153  /*--- Preprocessing of the geometry for all zones. In this routine, the edge-
154  based data structure is constructed, i.e. node and cell neighbors are
155  identified and linked, face areas and volumes of the dual mesh cells are
156  computed, and the multigrid levels are created using an agglomeration procedure. ---*/
157 
158  InitializeGeometry(config_container[iZone], geometry_container[iZone][iInst], dry_run);
159 
160  }
161  }
162 
163  /*--- Before we proceed with the zone loop we have to compute the wall distances.
164  * This computation depends on all zones at once. ---*/
165  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
166  cout << "Computing wall distances." << endl;
167 
168  CGeometry::ComputeWallDistance(config_container, geometry_container);
169 
170  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
171 
172  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
173 
174  /*--- Definition of the solver class: solver_container[#ZONES][#INSTANCES][#MG_GRIDS][#EQ_SYSTEMS].
175  The solver classes are specific to a particular set of governing equations,
176  and they contain the subroutines with instructions for computing each spatial
177  term of the PDE, i.e. loops over the edges to compute convective and viscous
178  fluxes, loops over the nodes to compute source terms, and routines for
179  imposing various boundary condition type for the PDE. ---*/
180 
181  InitializeSolver(config_container[iZone], geometry_container[iZone][iInst], solver_container[iZone][iInst]);
182 
183  /*--- Definition of the numerical method class:
184  numerics_container[#ZONES][#INSTANCES][#MG_GRIDS][#EQ_SYSTEMS][#EQ_TERMS].
185  The numerics class contains the implementation of the numerical methods for
186  evaluating convective or viscous fluxes between any two nodes in the edge-based
187  data structure (centered, upwind, galerkin), as well as any source terms
188  (piecewise constant reconstruction) evaluated in each dual mesh volume. ---*/
189 
190  InitializeNumerics(config_container[iZone], geometry_container[iZone][iInst],
191  solver_container[iZone][iInst], numerics_container[iZone][iInst]);
192 
193  /*--- Definition of the integration class: integration_container[#ZONES][#INSTANCES][#EQ_SYSTEMS].
194  The integration class orchestrates the execution of the spatial integration
195  subroutines contained in the solver class (including multigrid) for computing
196  the residual at each node, R(U) and then integrates the equations to a
197  steady state or time-accurately. ---*/
198 
199  InitializeIntegration(config_container[iZone], solver_container[iZone][iInst][MESH_0],
200  integration_container[iZone][iInst]);
201 
202  /*--- Instantiate the type of physics iteration to be executed within each zone. For
203  example, one can execute the same physics across multiple zones (mixing plane),
204  different physics in different zones (fluid-structure interaction), or couple multiple
205  systems tightly within a single zone by creating a new iteration class (e.g., RANS). ---*/
206 
207  PreprocessIteration(config_container[iZone], iteration_container[iZone][iInst]);
208 
209  /*--- Dynamic mesh processing. ---*/
210 
211  PreprocessDynamicMesh(config_container[iZone], geometry_container[iZone][iInst], solver_container[iZone][iInst],
212  iteration_container[iZone][iInst], grid_movement[iZone][iInst], surface_movement[iZone]);
213 
214  /*--- Static mesh processing. ---*/
215 
216  PreprocessStaticMesh(config_container[iZone], geometry_container[iZone][iInst]);
217 
218  }
219 
220  }
221 
222  /*! --- Compute the wall distance again to correctly compute the derivatives if we are running direct diff mode --- */
223  if (driver_config->GetDirectDiff() == D_DESIGN){
224  CGeometry::ComputeWallDistance(config_container, geometry_container);
225  }
226 
227  /*--- Definition of the interface and transfer conditions between different zones. ---*/
228 
229  if (nZone > 1) {
230  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
231  cout << endl <<"------------------- Multizone Interface Preprocessing -------------------" << endl;
232 
233  InitializeInterface(config_container, solver_container, geometry_container,
234  interface_types, interface_container, interpolator_container);
235  }
236 
237  if (fsi) {
238  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
239  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
240  RestartSolver(solver_container[iZone][iInst], geometry_container[iZone][iInst],
241  config_container[iZone], true);
242  }
243  }
244  }
245 
246  if (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetBoolTurbomachinery()){
247  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
248  cout << endl <<"---------------------- Turbomachinery Preprocessing ---------------------" << endl;
249 
250  PreprocessTurbomachinery(config_container, geometry_container, solver_container, interface_container, dummy_geo);
251  } else {
252  mixingplane = false;
253  }
254 
255 
256  PreprocessPythonInterface(config_container, geometry_container, solver_container);
257 
258 
259  /*--- Preprocessing time is reported now, but not included in the next compute portion. ---*/
260 
261  StopTime = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
262 
263  /*--- Compute/print the total time for performance benchmarking. ---*/
264 
265  UsedTime = StopTime-StartTime;
266  UsedTimePreproc = UsedTime;
267  UsedTimeCompute = 0.0;
268  UsedTimeOutput = 0.0;
269  IterCount = 0;
270  OutputCount = 0;
271  MDOFs = 0.0;
272  MDOFsDomain = 0.0;
273  Mpoints = 0.0;
274  MpointsDomain = 0.0;
275  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
276  Mpoints += geometry_container[iZone][INST_0][MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPoint()/(1.0e6);
277  MpointsDomain += geometry_container[iZone][INST_0][MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPointDomain()/(1.0e6);
278  MDOFs += DOFsPerPoint*geometry_container[iZone][INST_0][MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPoint()/(1.0e6);
279  MDOFsDomain += DOFsPerPoint*geometry_container[iZone][INST_0][MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPointDomain()/(1.0e6);
280  }
281 
282  /*--- Reset timer for compute/output performance benchmarking. ---*/
283 
284  StopTime = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
285 
286  /*--- Compute/print the total time for performance benchmarking. ---*/
287 
288  UsedTime = StopTime-StartTime;
289  UsedTimePreproc = UsedTime;
290 
291  /*--- Reset timer for compute performance benchmarking. ---*/
292 
293  StartTime = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
294 
295 }
296 
297 void CDriver::InitializeContainers(){
298 
299  /*--- Create pointers to all of the classes that may be used throughout
300  the SU2_CFD code. In general, the pointers are instantiated down a
301  hierarchy over all zones, multigrid levels, equation sets, and equation
302  terms as described in the comments below. ---*/
303 
304  iteration_container = nullptr;
305  output_container = nullptr;
306  integration_container = nullptr;
307  geometry_container = nullptr;
308  solver_container = nullptr;
309  numerics_container = nullptr;
310  config_container = nullptr;
311  surface_movement = nullptr;
312  grid_movement = nullptr;
313  FFDBox = nullptr;
314  interface_container = nullptr;
315  interface_types = nullptr;
316  nInst = nullptr;
317 
318  /*--- Definition and of the containers for all possible zones. ---*/
319 
320  iteration_container = new CIteration**[nZone] ();
321  solver_container = new CSolver****[nZone] ();
322  integration_container = new CIntegration***[nZone] ();
323  numerics_container = new CNumerics*****[nZone] ();
324  config_container = new CConfig*[nZone] ();
325  geometry_container = new CGeometry***[nZone] ();
326  surface_movement = new CSurfaceMovement*[nZone] ();
327  grid_movement = new CVolumetricMovement**[nZone] ();
328  FFDBox = new CFreeFormDefBox**[nZone] ();
329  interpolator_container.resize(nZone);
330  interface_container = new CInterface**[nZone] ();
331  interface_types = new unsigned short*[nZone] ();
332  output_container = new COutput*[nZone] ();
333  nInst = new unsigned short[nZone] ();
334  driver_config = nullptr;
335  driver_output = nullptr;
336 
337  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
338  interface_types[iZone] = new unsigned short[nZone];
339  nInst[iZone] = 1;
340  }
341 
342 }

345 void CDriver::Finalize() {
346 
347  const bool wrt_perf = config_container[ZONE_0]->GetWrt_Performance();
348 
349  /*--- Output some information to the console. ---*/
350 
351  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
352 
353  /*--- Print out the number of non-physical points and reconstructions ---*/
354 
355  if (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetNonphysical_Points() > 0)
356  cout << "Warning: there are " << config_container[ZONE_0]->GetNonphysical_Points() << " non-physical points in the solution." << endl;
357  if (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetNonphysical_Reconstr() > 0)
358  cout << "Warning: " << config_container[ZONE_0]->GetNonphysical_Reconstr() << " reconstructed states for upwinding are non-physical." << endl;
359  }
360 
361  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
362  cout <<"\n--------------------------- Finalizing Solver ---------------------------" << endl;
363 
364  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
365  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
366  FinalizeNumerics(numerics_container[iZone], solver_container[iZone][iInst],
367  geometry_container[iZone][iInst], config_container[iZone], iInst);
368  }
369  delete [] numerics_container[iZone];
370  }
371  delete [] numerics_container;
372  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CNumerics container." << endl;
373 
374  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
375  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
376  FinalizeIntegration(integration_container[iZone],
377  geometry_container[iZone][iInst],
378  config_container[iZone],
379  iInst);
380  }
381  delete [] integration_container[iZone];
382  }
383  delete [] integration_container;
384  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CIntegration container." << endl;
385 
386  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
387  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
388  FinalizeSolver(solver_container[iZone],
389  geometry_container[iZone][iInst],
390  config_container[iZone],
391  iInst);
392  }
393  delete [] solver_container[iZone];
394  }
395  delete [] solver_container;
396  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CSolver container." << endl;
397 
398  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
399  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++)
400  delete iteration_container[iZone][iInst];
401  delete [] iteration_container[iZone];
402  }
403  delete [] iteration_container;
404  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CIteration container." << endl;
405 
406  if (interface_container != nullptr) {
407  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
408  if (interface_container[iZone] != nullptr) {
409  for (unsigned short jZone = 0; jZone < nZone; jZone++)
410  delete interface_container[iZone][jZone];
411  delete [] interface_container[iZone];
412  }
413  }
414  delete [] interface_container;
415  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CInterface container." << endl;
416  }
417 
418  if (interface_types != nullptr) {
419  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++)
420  delete [] interface_types[iZone];
421  delete [] interface_types;
422  }
423 
424  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
425  if (geometry_container[iZone] != nullptr) {
426  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++){
427  for (unsigned short iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel < config_container[iZone]->GetnMGLevels()+1; iMGlevel++)
428  delete geometry_container[iZone][iInst][iMGlevel];
429  delete [] geometry_container[iZone][iInst];
430  }
431  delete [] geometry_container[iZone];
432  }
433  }
434  delete [] geometry_container;
435  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CGeometry container." << endl;
436 
437  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
438  delete [] FFDBox[iZone];
439  }
440  delete [] FFDBox;
441  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CFreeFormDefBox class." << endl;
442 
443  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
444  delete surface_movement[iZone];
445  }
446  delete [] surface_movement;
447  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CSurfaceMovement class." << endl;
448 
449  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
450  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++)
451  delete grid_movement[iZone][iInst];
452  delete [] grid_movement[iZone];
453  }
454  delete [] grid_movement;
455  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CVolumetricMovement class." << endl;
456 
457  /*--- Output profiling information ---*/
458  // Note that for now this is called only by a single thread, but all
459  // necessary variables have been made thread private for safety (tick/tock)!!
460 
461  config_container[ZONE_0]->SetProfilingCSV();
462  config_container[ZONE_0]->GEMMProfilingCSV();
463 
464  /*--- Deallocate config container ---*/
465  if (config_container!= nullptr) {
466  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++)
467  delete config_container[iZone];
468  delete [] config_container;
469  }
470  delete driver_config;
471  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted CConfig container." << endl;
472 
473  delete [] nInst;
474  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted nInst container." << endl;
475 
476  /*--- Deallocate output container ---*/
477 
478  if (output_container!= nullptr) {
479  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++)
480  delete output_container[iZone];
481  delete [] output_container;
482  }
483 
484  delete driver_output;
485 
486  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Deleted COutput class." << endl;
487 
488  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "-------------------------------------------------------------------------" << endl;
489 
490 
491  /*--- Stop the timer and output the final performance summary. ---*/
492 
493  StopTime = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
494 
495  UsedTime = StopTime-StartTime;
496  UsedTimeCompute += UsedTime;
497 
498  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (wrt_perf)) {
499  su2double TotalTime = UsedTimePreproc + UsedTimeCompute + UsedTimeOutput;
500  cout.precision(6);
501  cout << endl << endl <<"-------------------------- Performance Summary --------------------------" << endl;
502  cout << "Simulation totals:" << endl;
503  cout << setw(25) << "Wall-clock time (hrs):" << setw(12) << (TotalTime)/(60.0*60.0) << " | ";
504  cout << setw(20) << "Core-hrs:" << setw(12) << size*TotalTime/(60.0*60.0) << endl;
505  cout << setw(25) << "Cores:" << setw(12) << size << " | ";
506  cout << setw(20) << "DOFs/point:" << setw(12) << DOFsPerPoint << endl;
507  cout << setw(25) << "Points/core:" << setw(12) << 1.0e6*MpointsDomain/size << " | ";
508  cout << setw(20) << "Ghost points/core:" << setw(12) << 1.0e6*(Mpoints-MpointsDomain)/size << endl;
509  cout << setw(25) << "Ghost/Owned Point Ratio:" << setw(12) << (Mpoints-MpointsDomain)/MpointsDomain << " | " << endl;
510  cout << endl;
511  cout << "Preprocessing phase:" << endl;
512  cout << setw(25) << "Preproc. Time (s):" << setw(12)<< UsedTimePreproc << " | ";
513  cout << setw(20) << "Preproc. Time (%):" << setw(12)<< ((UsedTimePreproc * 100.0) / (TotalTime)) << endl;
514  cout << endl;
515  cout << "Compute phase:" << endl;
516  cout << setw(25) << "Compute Time (s):" << setw(12)<< UsedTimeCompute << " | ";
517  cout << setw(20) << "Compute Time (%):" << setw(12)<< ((UsedTimeCompute * 100.0) / (TotalTime)) << endl;
518  cout << setw(25) << "Iteration count:" << setw(12)<< IterCount << " | ";
519  if (IterCount != 0) {
520  cout << setw(20) << "Avg. s/iter:" << setw(12)<< UsedTimeCompute/IterCount << endl;
521  cout << setw(25) << "Core-s/iter/Mpoints:" << setw(12)<< size*UsedTimeCompute/IterCount/Mpoints << " | ";
522  cout << setw(20) << "Mpoints/s:" << setw(12)<< Mpoints*IterCount/UsedTimeCompute << endl;
523  } else cout << endl;
524  cout << endl;
525  cout << "Output phase:" << endl;
526  cout << setw(25) << "Output Time (s):" << setw(12)<< UsedTimeOutput << " | ";
527  cout << setw(20) << "Output Time (%):" << setw(12)<< ((UsedTimeOutput * 100.0) / (TotalTime)) << endl;
528  cout << setw(25) << "Output count:" << setw(12)<< OutputCount << " | ";
529  if (OutputCount != 0) {
530  cout << setw(20)<< "Avg. s/output:" << setw(12)<< UsedTimeOutput/OutputCount << endl;
531  if (BandwidthSum > 0) {
532  cout << setw(25)<< "Restart Aggr. BW (MB/s):" << setw(12)<< BandwidthSum/OutputCount << " | ";
533  cout << setw(20)<< "MB/s/core:" << setw(12)<< BandwidthSum/OutputCount/size << endl;
534  }
535  } else cout << endl;
536  cout << "-------------------------------------------------------------------------" << endl;
537  cout << endl;
538  }
539 
540  /*--- Exit the solver cleanly ---*/
541 
542  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
543  cout << endl <<"------------------------- Exit Success (SU2_CFD) ------------------------" << endl << endl;

600 void CDriver::InitializeGeometry(CConfig* config, CGeometry **&geometry, bool dummy){
601 
602  if (!dummy){
603  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
604  cout << endl <<"------------------- Geometry Preprocessing ( Zone " << config->GetiZone() <<" ) -------------------" << endl;
605 
606  if( fem_solver ) {
607  switch( config->GetKind_FEM_Flow() ) {
608  case DG: {
609  InitializeGeometryDGFEM(config, geometry);
610  break;
611  }
612  }
613  }
614  else {
615  InitializeGeometryFVM(config, geometry);
616  }
617  } else {
618  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
619  cout << endl <<"-------------------------- Using Dummy Geometry -------------------------" << endl;
620 
621  unsigned short iMGlevel;
622 
623  geometry = new CGeometry*[config->GetnMGLevels()+1] ();
624 
625  if (!fem_solver){
626  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
627  geometry[iMGlevel] = new CDummyGeometry(config);
628  }
629  } else {
630  geometry[MESH_0] = new CDummyMeshFEM_DG(config);
631  }
632 
633  nDim = geometry[MESH_0]->GetnDim();
634  }
635 
636  /*--- Computation of positive surface area in the z-plane which is used for
637  the calculation of force coefficient (non-dimensionalization). ---*/
638 
639  geometry[MESH_0]->SetPositive_ZArea(config);
640 
641  /*--- Set the actuator disk boundary conditions, if necessary. ---*/
642 
643  for (iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
644  geometry[iMesh]->MatchActuator_Disk(config);
645  }
646 
647  /*--- If we have any periodic markers in this calculation, we must
648  match the periodic points found on both sides of the periodic BC.
649  Note that the current implementation requires a 1-to-1 matching of
650  periodic points on the pair of periodic faces after the translation
651  or rotation is taken into account. ---*/
652 
653  if ((config->GetnMarker_Periodic() != 0) && !fem_solver) {
654  for (iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
655 
656  /*--- Note that we loop over pairs of periodic markers individually
657  so that repeated nodes on adjacent periodic faces are properly
658  accounted for in multiple places. ---*/
659 
660  for (unsigned short iPeriodic = 1; iPeriodic <= config->GetnMarker_Periodic()/2; iPeriodic++) {
661  geometry[iMesh]->MatchPeriodic(config, iPeriodic);
662  }
663 
664  /*--- For Streamwise Periodic flow, find a unique reference node on the dedicated inlet marker. ---*/
665  if (config->GetKind_Streamwise_Periodic() != ENUM_STREAMWISE_PERIODIC::NONE)
666  geometry[iMesh]->FindUniqueNode_PeriodicBound(config);
667 
668  /*--- Initialize the communication framework for the periodic BCs. ---*/
669  geometry[iMesh]->PreprocessPeriodicComms(geometry[iMesh], config);
670 
671  }
672  }
673 
674  /*--- If activated by the compile directive, perform a partition analysis. ---*/
675 #if PARTITION
676  if (!dummy){
677  if( fem_solver ) Partition_Analysis_FEM(geometry[MESH_0], config);
678  else Partition_Analysis(geometry[MESH_0], config);
679  }
680 #endif
681 
682  /*--- Keep a reference to the main (ZONE_0, INST_0, MESH_0) geometry. ---*/
683 
684  main_geometry = geometry_container[ZONE_0][INST_0][MESH_0];
685 }

687 void CDriver::InitializeGeometryFVM(CConfig *config, CGeometry **&geometry) {
688 
689  unsigned short iZone = config->GetiZone(), iMGlevel;
690  unsigned short requestedMGlevels = config->GetnMGLevels();
691  const bool fea = config->GetStructuralProblem();
692 
693  /*--- Definition of the geometry class to store the primal grid in the partitioning process.
694  * All ranks process the grid and call ParMETIS for partitioning ---*/
695 
696  CGeometry *geometry_aux = new CPhysicalGeometry(config, iZone, nZone);
697 
698  /*--- Set the dimension --- */
699 
700  nDim = geometry_aux->GetnDim();
701 
702  /*--- Color the initial grid and set the send-receive domains (ParMETIS) ---*/
703 
704  geometry_aux->SetColorGrid_Parallel(config);
705 
706  /*--- Allocate the memory of the current domain, and divide the grid
707  between the ranks. ---*/
708 
709  geometry = new CGeometry *[config->GetnMGLevels()+1] ();
710 
711  /*--- Build the grid data structures using the ParMETIS coloring. ---*/
712 
713  geometry[MESH_0] = new CPhysicalGeometry(geometry_aux, config);
714 
715  /*--- Deallocate the memory of geometry_aux and solver_aux ---*/
716 
717  delete geometry_aux;
718 
719  /*--- Add the Send/Receive boundaries ---*/
720  geometry[MESH_0]->SetSendReceive(config);
721 
722  /*--- Add the Send/Receive boundaries ---*/
723  geometry[MESH_0]->SetBoundaries(config);
724 
725  /*--- Compute elements surrounding points, points surrounding points ---*/
726 
727  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Setting point connectivity." << endl;
728  geometry[MESH_0]->SetPoint_Connectivity();
729 
730  /*--- Renumbering points using Reverse Cuthill McKee ordering ---*/
731 
732  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Renumbering points (Reverse Cuthill McKee Ordering)." << endl;
733  geometry[MESH_0]->SetRCM_Ordering(config);
734 
735  /*--- recompute elements surrounding points, points surrounding points ---*/
736 
737  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Recomputing point connectivity." << endl;
738  geometry[MESH_0]->SetPoint_Connectivity();
739 
740  /*--- Compute elements surrounding elements ---*/
741 
742  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Setting element connectivity." << endl;
743  geometry[MESH_0]->SetElement_Connectivity();
744 
745  /*--- Check the orientation before computing geometrical quantities ---*/
746 
747  geometry[MESH_0]->SetBoundVolume();
748  if (config->GetReorientElements()) {
749  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Checking the numerical grid orientation." << endl;
750  geometry[MESH_0]->Check_IntElem_Orientation(config);
751  geometry[MESH_0]->Check_BoundElem_Orientation(config);
752  }
753 
754  /*--- Create the edge structure ---*/
755 
756  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Identifying edges and vertices." << endl;
757  geometry[MESH_0]->SetEdges();
758  geometry[MESH_0]->SetVertex(config);
759 
760  /*--- Create the control volume structures ---*/
761 
762  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Setting the control volume structure." << endl;
763  SU2_OMP_PARALLEL {
764  geometry[MESH_0]->SetControlVolume(config, ALLOCATE);
765  geometry[MESH_0]->SetBoundControlVolume(config, ALLOCATE);
766  }
767  END_SU2_OMP_PARALLEL
768 
769  /*--- Visualize a dual control volume if requested ---*/
770 
771  if ((config->GetVisualize_CV() >= 0) &&
772  (config->GetVisualize_CV() < (long)geometry[MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPointDomain()))
773  geometry[MESH_0]->VisualizeControlVolume(config);
774 
775  /*--- Identify closest normal neighbor ---*/
776 
777  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Searching for the closest normal neighbors to the surfaces." << endl;
778  geometry[MESH_0]->FindNormal_Neighbor(config);
779 
780  /*--- Store the global to local mapping. ---*/
781 
782  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Storing a mapping from global to local point index." << endl;
783  geometry[MESH_0]->SetGlobal_to_Local_Point();
784 
785  /*--- Compute the surface curvature ---*/
786 
787  if (!fea) {
788  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Compute the surface curvature." << endl;
789  geometry[MESH_0]->ComputeSurf_Curvature(config);
790  }
791 
792  /*--- Compute the global surface areas for all markers. ---*/
793 
794  geometry[MESH_0]->ComputeSurfaceAreaCfgFile(config);
795 
796  /*--- Check for periodicity and disable MG if necessary. ---*/
797 
798  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "Checking for periodicity." << endl;
799  geometry[MESH_0]->Check_Periodicity(config);
800 
801  /*--- Compute mesh quality statistics on the fine grid. ---*/
802 
803  if (!fea) {
804  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
805  cout << "Computing mesh quality statistics for the dual control volumes." << endl;
806  geometry[MESH_0]->ComputeMeshQualityStatistics(config);
807  }
808 
809  geometry[MESH_0]->SetMGLevel(MESH_0);
810  if ((config->GetnMGLevels() != 0) && (rank == MASTER_NODE))
811  cout << "Setting the multigrid structure." << endl;
812 
813  /*--- Loop over all the new grid ---*/
814 
815  for (iMGlevel = 1; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
816 
817  /*--- Create main agglomeration structure ---*/
818 
819  geometry[iMGlevel] = new CMultiGridGeometry(geometry[iMGlevel-1], config, iMGlevel);
820 
821  /*--- Compute points surrounding points. ---*/
822 
823  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetPoint_Connectivity(geometry[iMGlevel-1]);
824 
825  /*--- Create the edge structure ---*/
826 
827  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetEdges();
828  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetVertex(geometry[iMGlevel-1], config);
829 
830  /*--- Create the control volume structures ---*/
831 
832  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetControlVolume(geometry[iMGlevel-1], ALLOCATE);
833  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetBoundControlVolume(geometry[iMGlevel-1], config, ALLOCATE);
834  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetCoord(geometry[iMGlevel-1]);
835 
836  /*--- Find closest neighbor to a surface point ---*/
837 
838  geometry[iMGlevel]->FindNormal_Neighbor(config);
839 
840  /*--- Store our multigrid index. ---*/
841 
842  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetMGLevel(iMGlevel);
843 
844  /*--- Protect against the situation that we were not able to complete
845  the agglomeration for this level, i.e., there weren't enough points.
846  We need to check if we changed the total number of levels and delete
847  the incomplete CMultiGridGeometry object. ---*/
848 
849  if (config->GetnMGLevels() != requestedMGlevels) {
850  delete geometry[iMGlevel];
851  geometry[iMGlevel] = nullptr;
852  break;
853  }
854 
855  }
856 
857  if (config->GetWrt_MultiGrid()) geometry[MESH_0]->ColorMGLevels(config->GetnMGLevels(), geometry);
858 
859  /*--- For unsteady simulations, initialize the grid volumes
860  and coordinates for previous solutions. Loop over all zones/grids ---*/
861 
862  if ((config->GetTime_Marching() != TIME_MARCHING::STEADY) && config->GetDynamic_Grid()) {
863  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
864 
865  /*--- Update cell volume ---*/
866  geometry[iMGlevel]->nodes->SetVolume_n();
867  geometry[iMGlevel]->nodes->SetVolume_nM1();
868 
869  if (config->GetGrid_Movement()) {
870  /*--- Update point coordinates ---*/
871  geometry[iMGlevel]->nodes->SetCoord_n();
872  geometry[iMGlevel]->nodes->SetCoord_n1();
873  }
874  }
875  }
876 
877 
878  /*--- Create the data structure for MPI point-to-point communications. ---*/
879 
880  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++)
881  geometry[iMGlevel]->PreprocessP2PComms(geometry[iMGlevel], config);
882 
883 
884  /*--- Perform a few preprocessing routines and communications. ---*/
885 
886  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
887 
888  /*--- Compute the max length. ---*/
889 
890  if (!fea) {
891  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (iMGlevel == MESH_0))
892  cout << "Finding max control volume width." << endl;
893  geometry[iMGlevel]->SetMaxLength(config);
894  }
895 
896  /*--- Communicate the number of neighbors. This is needed for
897  some centered schemes and for multigrid in parallel. ---*/
898 
899  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size > SINGLE_NODE) && (iMGlevel == MESH_0))
900  cout << "Communicating number of neighbors." << endl;
901  geometry[iMGlevel]->InitiateComms(geometry[iMGlevel], config, MPI_QUANTITIES::NEIGHBORS);
902  geometry[iMGlevel]->CompleteComms(geometry[iMGlevel], config, MPI_QUANTITIES::NEIGHBORS);
903  }
904 
905 }

907 void CDriver::InitializeGeometryDGFEM(CConfig* config, CGeometry **&geometry) {
908 
909  /*--- Definition of the geometry class to store the primal grid in the partitioning process. ---*/
910  /*--- All ranks process the grid and call ParMETIS for partitioning ---*/

935

937  delete solver_aux;
938 
939  /*--- Add the Send/Receive boundaries ---*/
940  geometry[MESH_0]->SetSendReceive(config);
941 
942  /*--- Add the Send/Receive boundaries ---*/
943  geometry[MESH_0]->SetBoundaries(config);

961 
962  /*--- Compute the metric terms of the surface elements. ---*/

964  DGMesh->MetricTermsSurfaceElements(config);

987 
988 
989  /*--- Loop to create the coarser grid levels. ---*/
990 
991  for(unsigned short iMGlevel=1; iMGlevel<=config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
992

999 void CDriver::InitializeSolver(CConfig* config, CGeometry** geometry, CSolver ***&solver) {
1000 
1001  MAIN_SOLVER kindSolver = config->GetKind_Solver();
1002 
1003  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
1004  cout << endl <<"-------------------- Solver Preprocessing ( Zone " << config->GetiZone() <<" ) --------------------" << endl;
1005 
1006  solver = new CSolver**[config->GetnMGLevels()+1] ();
1007 
1008  for (iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++){
1009  solver[iMesh] = CSolverFactory::CreateSolverContainer(kindSolver, config, geometry[iMesh], iMesh);
1010  }
1011 
1012  /*--- Count the number of DOFs per solution point. ---*/
1013 
1014  DOFsPerPoint = 0;
1015 
1016  for (unsigned int iSol = 0; iSol < MAX_SOLS; iSol++)
1017  if (solver[MESH_0][iSol]) DOFsPerPoint += solver[MESH_0][iSol]->GetnVar();
1018 
1019  /*--- Restart solvers, for FSI the geometry cannot be updated because the interpolation classes
1020  * should always use the undeformed mesh (otherwise the results would not be repeatable). ---*/
1021 
1022  if (!fsi) RestartSolver(solver, geometry, config, true);
1023 
1024  /*--- Set up any necessary inlet profiles ---*/
1025 
1026  PreprocessInlet(solver, geometry, config);
1027 
1028 }

1030 void CDriver::PreprocessInlet(CSolver ***solver, CGeometry **geometry, CConfig *config) const {
1031 
1032  /*--- Adjust iteration number for unsteady restarts. ---*/
1033 
1034  const bool adjoint = config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint() || config->GetContinuous_Adjoint();
1035 
1036  int val_iter = 0;
1037 
1038  if (config->GetTime_Domain()) {
1039  val_iter = adjoint? config->GetUnst_AdjointIter() : config->GetRestart_Iter();
1040  val_iter -= 1;
1041  if (!adjoint && config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND)
1042  val_iter -= 1;
1043  if (!adjoint && !config->GetRestart()) val_iter = 0;
1044  }
1045 
1046  /*--- Load inlet profile files for any of the active solver containers.
1047  Note that these routines fill the fine grid data structures for the markers
1048  and restrict values down to all coarser MG levels. ---*/
1049 
1050  if (config->GetInlet_Profile_From_File()) {
1051 
1052  /*--- Use LoadInletProfile() routines for the particular solver. ---*/
1053 
1054  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1055  cout << "\nReading inlet profile from file: " << config->GetInlet_FileName() << endl;
1056  }
1057 
1058  for (const auto marker_type : {INLET_FLOW, SUPERSONIC_INLET}) {
1059  if (solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]) {
1060  solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->LoadInletProfile(geometry, solver, config, val_iter, FLOW_SOL, marker_type);
1061  }
1062  if (solver[MESH_0][TURB_SOL]) {
1063  solver[MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->LoadInletProfile(geometry, solver, config, val_iter, TURB_SOL, marker_type);
1064  }
1065  if (solver[MESH_0][SPECIES_SOL]) {
1066  solver[MESH_0][SPECIES_SOL]->LoadInletProfile(geometry, solver, config, val_iter, SPECIES_SOL, marker_type);
1067  }
1068  }
1069 
1070  /*--- Exit if profiles were requested for a solver that is not available. ---*/
1071 
1072  if (!config->GetFluidProblem()) {
1073  SU2_MPI::Error("Inlet profile specification via file (C++) has not been \n"
1074  "implemented yet for this solver.\n"
1075  "Please set SPECIFIED_INLET_PROFILE= NO and try again.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1076  }
1077 
1078  } else {
1079 
1080  /*--- Uniform inlets or python-customized inlets ---*/
1081 
1082  /* --- Initialize quantities for inlet boundary
1083  * This routine does not check if the python wrapper is being used to
1084  * set custom boundary conditions. This is intentional; the
1085  * default values for python custom BCs are initialized with the default
1086  * values specified in the config (avoiding non physical values) --- */
1087 
1088  for (unsigned short iMesh = 0; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
1089  for(unsigned short iMarker=0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
1090  if (solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]) solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->SetUniformInlet(config, iMarker);
1091  if (solver[iMesh][TURB_SOL]) solver[iMesh][TURB_SOL]->SetUniformInlet(config, iMarker);
1092  if (solver[iMesh][TRANS_SOL]) solver[iMesh][TRANS_SOL]->SetUniformInlet(config, iMarker);
1093  if (solver[iMesh][SPECIES_SOL]) solver[iMesh][SPECIES_SOL]->SetUniformInlet(config, iMarker);
1094  }
1095  }
1096 
1097  }
1098 
1099 }

1101 void CDriver::RestartSolver(CSolver ***solver, CGeometry **geometry,
1102  CConfig *config, bool update_geo) {
1103 
1104  /*--- Check for restarts and use the LoadRestart() routines. ---*/
1105 
1106  const bool restart = config->GetRestart();
1107  const bool restart_flow = config->GetRestart_Flow();
1108 
1109  /*--- Adjust iteration number for unsteady restarts. ---*/
1110 
1111  int val_iter = 0;
1112 
1113  const bool adjoint = (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint() || config->GetContinuous_Adjoint());
1114  const bool time_domain = config->GetTime_Domain();
1115  const bool dt_step_2nd = (config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND) &&
1116  !config->GetStructuralProblem() && !config->GetFEMSolver() &&
1117  !adjoint && time_domain;
1118 
1119  if (time_domain) {
1120  if (adjoint) val_iter = config->GetUnst_AdjointIter() - 1;
1121  else val_iter = config->GetRestart_Iter() - 1 - dt_step_2nd;
1122  }
1123 
1124  /*--- Restart direct solvers. ---*/
1125 
1126  if (restart || restart_flow) {
1127  for (auto iSol = 0u; iSol < MAX_SOLS; ++iSol) {
1128  auto sol = solver[MESH_0][iSol];
1129  if (sol && !sol->GetAdjoint()) {
1130  /*--- Note that the mesh solver always loads the most recent file (and not -2). ---*/
1131  SU2_OMP_PARALLEL_(if(sol->GetHasHybridParallel()))
1132  sol->LoadRestart(geometry, solver, config, val_iter + (iSol==MESH_SOL && dt_step_2nd), update_geo);
1133  END_SU2_OMP_PARALLEL
1134  }
1135  }
1136  }
1137 
1138  /*--- Restart adjoint solvers. ---*/
1139 
1140  if (restart) {
1141  if ((config->GetKind_Solver() == MAIN_SOLVER::TEMPLATE_SOLVER) ||
1142  (config->GetKind_Solver() == MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_RANS && !config->GetFrozen_Visc_Cont())) {
1143  SU2_MPI::Error("A restart capability has not been implemented yet for this solver.\n"
1144  "Please set RESTART_SOL= NO and try again.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1145  }
1146 
1147  for (auto iSol = 0u; iSol < MAX_SOLS; ++iSol) {
1148  auto sol = solver[MESH_0][iSol];
1149  if (sol && sol->GetAdjoint())
1150  sol->LoadRestart(geometry, solver, config, val_iter, update_geo);
1151  }
1152  }
1153 
1154 }

1162  }

1165  delete [] solver[val_iInst];

1192 template <class Indices>
1193 void CDriver::InstantiateTurbulentNumerics(unsigned short nVar_Turb, int offset, const CConfig *config,
1194  const CSolver* turb_solver, CNumerics ****&numerics) const {
1195  const int conv_term = CONV_TERM + offset;
1196  const int visc_term = VISC_TERM + offset;
1197 
1198  const int source_first_term = SOURCE_FIRST_TERM + offset;
1199  const int source_second_term = SOURCE_SECOND_TERM + offset;
1200 
1201  const int conv_bound_term = CONV_BOUND_TERM + offset;
1202  const int visc_bound_term = VISC_BOUND_TERM + offset;
1203 
1204  /*--- Assign turbulence model booleans ---*/
1205 
1206  bool spalart_allmaras = false, menter_sst = false;
1207 
1208  switch (config->GetKind_Turb_Model()) {
1209  case TURB_MODEL::NONE:
1210  SU2_MPI::Error("No turbulence model selected.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1211  break;
1212  case TURB_MODEL::SA:
1213  spalart_allmaras = true;
1214  break;
1215  case TURB_MODEL::SST:
1216  menter_sst = true;
1217  break;
1218  }
1219 
1220  /*--- If the Menter SST model is used, store the constants of the model and determine the
1221  free stream values of the turbulent kinetic energy and dissipation rate. ---*/
1222 
1223  const su2double *constants = nullptr;
1224  su2double kine_Inf = 0.0, omega_Inf = 0.0;
1225 
1226  if (menter_sst) {
1227  constants = turb_solver->GetConstants();
1228  kine_Inf = turb_solver->GetTke_Inf();
1229  omega_Inf = turb_solver->GetOmega_Inf();
1230  }
1231 
1232  /*--- Definition of the convective scheme for each equation and mesh level ---*/
1233 
1234  switch (config->GetKind_ConvNumScheme_Turb()) {
1235  case NO_CONVECTIVE:
1236  SU2_MPI::Error("Config file is missing the CONV_NUM_METHOD_TURB option.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1237  break;
1238  case SPACE_UPWIND :
1239  for (auto iMGlevel = 0u; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
1240  if (spalart_allmaras) {
1241  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][conv_term] = new CUpwSca_TurbSA<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, config);
1242  }
1243  else if (menter_sst)
1244  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][conv_term] = new CUpwSca_TurbSST<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, config);
1245  }
1246  break;
1247  default:
1248  SU2_MPI::Error("Invalid convective scheme for the turbulence equations.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1249  break;
1250  }
1251 
1252  /*--- Definition of the viscous scheme for each equation and mesh level ---*/
1253 
1254  for (auto iMGlevel = 0u; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
1255  if (spalart_allmaras) {
1256  if (config->GetSAParsedOptions().version == SA_OPTIONS::NEG) {
1257  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSA_Neg<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, true, config);
1258  } else {
1259  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSA<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, true, config);
1260  }
1261  }
1262  else if (menter_sst)
1263  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSST<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, constants, true, config);
1264  }
1265 
1266  /*--- Definition of the source term integration scheme for each equation and mesh level ---*/
1267 
1268  for (auto iMGlevel = 0u; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
1269  auto& turb_source_first_term = numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][source_first_term];
1270 
1271  if (spalart_allmaras)
1272  turb_source_first_term = SAFactory<Indices>(nDim, config);
1273  else if (menter_sst)
1274  turb_source_first_term = new CSourcePieceWise_TurbSST<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, constants, kine_Inf, omega_Inf,
1275  config);
1276 
1277  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][source_second_term] = new CSourceNothing(nDim, nVar_Turb, config);
1278  }
1279 
1280  /*--- Definition of the boundary condition method ---*/
1281 
1282  for (auto iMGlevel = 0u; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
1283  if (spalart_allmaras) {
1284  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][conv_bound_term] = new CUpwSca_TurbSA<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, config);
1285 
1286  if (config->GetSAParsedOptions().version == SA_OPTIONS::NEG) {
1287  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_bound_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSA_Neg<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, false, config);
1288  } else {
1289  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_bound_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSA<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, false, config);
1290  }
1291  }
1292  else if (menter_sst) {
1293  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][conv_bound_term] = new CUpwSca_TurbSST<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, config);
1294  numerics[iMGlevel][TURB_SOL][visc_bound_term] = new CAvgGrad_TurbSST<Indices>(nDim, nVar_Turb, constants, false,
1295  config);
1296  }
1297  }
1298 }

1432 void CDriver::InitializeNumerics(CConfig *config, CGeometry **geometry, CSolver ***solver, CNumerics ****&numerics) const {
1433 
1434  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
1435  cout << endl <<"------------------- Numerics Preprocessing ( Zone " << config->GetiZone() <<" ) -------------------" << endl;
1436 
1437  unsigned short iMGlevel, iSol,
1438  nVar_Template = 0,
1439  nVar_Flow = 0,
1440  nVar_NEMO = 0,
1441  nPrimVar_NEMO = 0,
1442  nPrimVarGrad_NEMO = 0,
1443  nVar_Trans = 0,
1444  nVar_Turb = 0,
1445  nVar_Species = 0,
1446  nVar_Adj_Flow = 0,
1447  nVar_Adj_Turb = 0,
1448  nVar_FEM = 0,
1449  nVar_Rad = 0;
1450 
1451  numerics = new CNumerics***[config->GetnMGLevels()+1] ();
1452 
1453  bool compressible = false;
1454  bool incompressible = false;
1455  bool ideal_gas = (config->GetKind_FluidModel() == STANDARD_AIR) || (config->GetKind_FluidModel() == IDEAL_GAS);
1456  bool roe_low_dissipation = (config->GetKind_RoeLowDiss() != NO_ROELOWDISS);
1457 
1458  /*--- Initialize some useful booleans ---*/
1459  bool euler, ns, NEMO_euler, NEMO_ns, turbulent, adj_euler, adj_ns, adj_turb, fem_euler, fem_ns;
1460  bool fem, heat, transition, template_solver;
1461 
1462  euler = ns = NEMO_euler = NEMO_ns = turbulent = adj_euler = adj_ns = adj_turb = fem_euler = fem_ns = false;
1463  fem = heat = transition = template_solver = false;
1464  bool species = false;
1465 
1466  /*--- Assign booleans ---*/
1467  switch (config->GetKind_Solver()) {
1468  case MAIN_SOLVER::TEMPLATE_SOLVER:
1469  template_solver = true; break;
1470 
1471  case MAIN_SOLVER::EULER:
1472  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_EULER:
1473  euler = compressible = true; break;
1474 
1475  case MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES:
1476  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES:
1477  ns = compressible = true;
1478  species = (config->GetKind_Species_Model() != SPECIES_MODEL::NONE); break;
1479 
1480  case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER:
1481  NEMO_euler = compressible = true; break;
1482 
1483  case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
1484  NEMO_ns = compressible = true; break;
1485 
1486  case MAIN_SOLVER::RANS:
1487  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS:
1488  ns = compressible = turbulent = true;
1489  transition = (config->GetKind_Trans_Model() == TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM);
1490  species = config->GetKind_Species_Model() != SPECIES_MODEL::NONE; break;
1491 
1492  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER:
1493  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_EULER:
1494  euler = incompressible = true; break;
1495 
1496  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES:
1497  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES:
1498  ns = incompressible = true;
1499  heat = config->GetWeakly_Coupled_Heat();
1500  species = (config->GetKind_Species_Model() != SPECIES_MODEL::NONE); break;
1501 
1502  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS:
1503  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS:
1504  ns = incompressible = turbulent = true;
1505  heat = config->GetWeakly_Coupled_Heat();
1506  transition = (config->GetKind_Trans_Model() == TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM);
1507  species = (config->GetKind_Species_Model() != SPECIES_MODEL::NONE); break;
1508 
1509  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER:
1510  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_EULER:
1511  fem_euler = compressible = true; break;
1512 
1513  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES:
1514  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_NS:
1515  fem_ns = compressible = true; break;
1516 
1517  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS:
1518  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_RANS:
1519  fem_ns = compressible = true; break;
1520 
1521  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_LES:
1522  fem_ns = compressible = true; break;
1523 
1524  case MAIN_SOLVER::HEAT_EQUATION:
1525  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_HEAT:
1526  heat = true; break;
1527 
1528  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY:
1529  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM:
1530  fem = true; break;
1531 
1532  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_EULER:
1533  adj_euler = euler = compressible = true; break;
1534 
1535  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES:
1536  adj_ns = ns = compressible = true;
1537  turbulent = (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() != TURB_MODEL::NONE); break;
1538 
1539  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_RANS:
1540  adj_ns = ns = compressible = turbulent = true;
1541  adj_turb = !config->GetFrozen_Visc_Cont(); break;
1542 
1543  default:
1544  break;
1545 
1546  }
1547 
1548  /*--- Number of variables for the template ---*/
1549 
1550  if (template_solver) nVar_Flow = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1551 
1552  /*--- Number of variables for direct problem ---*/
1553 
1554  if (euler) nVar_Flow = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1555  if (ns) nVar_Flow = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1556  if (NEMO_euler) nVar_NEMO = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1557  if (NEMO_ns) nVar_NEMO = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1558  if (turbulent) nVar_Turb = solver[MESH_0][TURB_SOL]->GetnVar();
1559  if (transition) nVar_Trans = solver[MESH_0][TRANS_SOL]->GetnVar();
1560  if (species) nVar_Species = solver[MESH_0][SPECIES_SOL]->GetnVar();
1561 
1562  if (fem_euler) nVar_Flow = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1563  if (fem_ns) nVar_Flow = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1564 
1565  if (fem) nVar_FEM = solver[MESH_0][FEA_SOL]->GetnVar();
1566 
1567  if (config->AddRadiation()) nVar_Rad = solver[MESH_0][RAD_SOL]->GetnVar();
1568 
1569  /*--- Number of variables for adjoint problem ---*/
1570 
1571  if (adj_euler) nVar_Adj_Flow = solver[MESH_0][ADJFLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1572  if (adj_ns) nVar_Adj_Flow = solver[MESH_0][ADJFLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
1573  if (adj_turb) nVar_Adj_Turb = solver[MESH_0][ADJTURB_SOL]->GetnVar();
1574 
1575  /*--- Additional Variables required for NEMO solver ---*/
1576 
1577  if (NEMO_euler || NEMO_ns) nPrimVar_NEMO = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnPrimVar();
1578  if (NEMO_euler || NEMO_ns) nPrimVarGrad_NEMO = solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnPrimVarGrad();
1579 
1580  /*--- Definition of the Class for the numerical method:
1581  numerics_container[INSTANCE_LEVEL][MESH_LEVEL][EQUATION][EQ_TERM] ---*/
1582 
1583  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
1584  numerics[iMGlevel] = new CNumerics** [MAX_SOLS];
1585  for (iSol = 0; iSol < MAX_SOLS; iSol++)
1586  numerics[iMGlevel][iSol] = new CNumerics* [MAX_TERMS*omp_get_max_threads()]();
1587  }
1588 
1589  /*--- Instantiate one numerics object per thread for each required term. ---*/
1590 
1591  for (int thread = 0; thread < omp_get_max_threads(); ++thread)
1592  {
1593  const int offset = thread * MAX_TERMS;
1594 
1595  const int conv_term = CONV_TERM + offset;
1596  const int visc_term = VISC_TERM + offset;
1597 
1598  const int source_first_term = SOURCE_FIRST_TERM + offset;
1599  const int source_second_term = SOURCE_SECOND_TERM + offset;
1600 
1601  const int conv_bound_term = CONV_BOUND_TERM + offset;
1602  const int visc_bound_term = VISC_BOUND_TERM + offset;
1603 
1604  const int fea_term = FEA_TERM + offset;
1605 
1606  /*--- Solver definition for the template problem ---*/
1607  if (template_solver) {

2366 void CDriver::PreprocessDynamicMesh(CConfig *config, CGeometry **geometry, CSolver ***solver, CIteration* iteration,
2367  CVolumetricMovement *&grid_movement, CSurfaceMovement *&surface_movement) const{
2368 
2369  /*--- Instantiate the geometry movement classes for the solution of unsteady
2370  flows on dynamic meshes, including rigid mesh transformations, dynamically
2371  deforming meshes, and preprocessing of harmonic balance. ---*/
2372 
2373  if (!fem_solver && (config->GetGrid_Movement() || (config->GetDirectDiff() == D_DESIGN))) {
2374  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
2375  cout << "Setting dynamic mesh structure for zone "<< iZone + 1<<"." << endl;
2376  grid_movement = new CVolumetricMovement(geometry[MESH_0], config);
2377 
2378  if (surface_movement == nullptr)
2379  surface_movement = new CSurfaceMovement();
2380 
2381  surface_movement->CopyBoundary(geometry[MESH_0], config);
2382  if (config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::HARMONIC_BALANCE){
2383  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << endl << "Instance "<< iInst + 1 <<":" << endl;
2384  iteration->SetGrid_Movement(geometry, surface_movement, grid_movement, solver, config, 0, iInst);
2385  }
2386  }
2387 
2388  if (config->GetDirectDiff() == D_DESIGN) {
2389  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
2390  cout << "Setting surface/volume derivatives." << endl;
2391 
2392  /*--- Set the surface derivatives, i.e. the derivative of the surface mesh nodes with respect to the design variables ---*/
2393 
2394  surface_movement->SetSurface_Derivative(geometry[MESH_0],config);
2395 
2396  /*--- Call the volume deformation routine with derivative mode enabled.
2397  This computes the derivative of the volume mesh with respect to the surface nodes ---*/
2398 
2399  grid_movement->SetVolume_Deformation(geometry[MESH_0],config, true, true);
2400 
2401  /*--- Update the multi-grid structure to propagate the derivative information to the coarser levels ---*/
2402 
2403  CGeometry::UpdateGeometry(geometry,config);
2404 
2405  }
2406

2409 void CDriver::InitializeInterface(CConfig **config, CSolver***** solver, CGeometry**** geometry,
2410  unsigned short** interface_types, CInterface ***interface,
2411  vector<vector<unique_ptr<CInterpolator> > >& interpolation) {
2412 
2413  /*--- Setup interpolation and transfer for all possible donor/target pairs. ---*/
2414 
2415  for (auto target = 0u; target < nZone; target++) {
2416 
2417  for (auto donor = 0u; donor < nZone; donor++) {
2418 
2419  /*--- Aliases to make code less verbose. ---*/
2420  auto& interface_type = interface_types[donor][target];
2421 
2422  if (donor == target) {
2423  interface_type = ZONES_ARE_EQUAL;
2424  continue;
2425  }
2426  interface_type = NO_TRANSFER;
2427 
2428  /*--- If there is a common interface setup the interpolation and transfer. ---*/
2429 
2430  if (!CInterpolator::CheckZonesInterface(config[donor], config[target])) {
2431  interface_type = NO_COMMON_INTERFACE;
2432  }
2433  else {
2434  /*--- Begin the creation of the communication pattern among zones. ---*/
2435 
2436  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "From zone " << donor << " to zone " << target << ":" << endl;
2437 
2438  /*--- Setup the interpolation. ---*/
2439 
2440  interpolation[donor][target] = unique_ptr<CInterpolator>(CInterpolatorFactory::CreateInterpolator(
2441  geometry, config, interpolation[target][donor].get(), donor, target));
2442 
2443  /*--- The type of variables transferred depends on the donor/target physics. ---*/
2444 
2445  const bool heat_target = config[target]->GetHeatProblem();
2446  const bool fluid_target = config[target]->GetFluidProblem();
2447  const bool structural_target = config[target]->GetStructuralProblem();
2448 
2449  const bool heat_donor = config[donor]->GetHeatProblem();
2450  const bool fluid_donor = config[donor]->GetFluidProblem();
2451  const bool structural_donor = config[donor]->GetStructuralProblem();
2452 
2453  /*--- Initialize the appropriate transfer strategy. ---*/
2454 
2455  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << " Transferring ";
2456 
2457  if (fluid_donor && structural_target) {
2458  interface_type = FLOW_TRACTION;
2459  auto nConst = 2;
2460  bool conservative = config[target]->GetConservativeInterpolation();
2461  if(!config[ZONE_0]->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()) {
2462  interface[donor][target] = new CFlowTractionInterface(nDim, nConst, config[donor], conservative);
2463  } else {
2464  interface[donor][target] = new CDiscAdjFlowTractionInterface(nDim, nConst, config[donor], conservative);
2465  }
2466  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "fluid " << (conservative? "forces." : "tractions.") << endl;
2467  }
2468  else if (structural_donor && (fluid_target || heat_target)) {
2469  if (solver_container[target][INST_0][MESH_0][MESH_SOL] == nullptr) {
2470  SU2_MPI::Error("Mesh deformation was not correctly specified for the fluid/heat zone.\n"
2471  "Use DEFORM_MESH=YES, and setup MARKER_DEFORM_MESH=(...)", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2472  }
2473  interface_type = BOUNDARY_DISPLACEMENTS;
2474  if (!config[donor]->GetTime_Domain()) interface[donor][target] = new CDisplacementsInterface(nDim, 0);
2475  else interface[donor][target] = new CDisplacementsInterface(2*nDim, 0);
2476  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "boundary displacements from the structural solver." << endl;
2477  }
2478  else if (fluid_donor && fluid_target) {
2479  /*--- Interface handling for turbomachinery applications. ---*/
2480  if (config[donor]->GetBoolTurbomachinery()) {
2481  auto interfaceIndex = donor+target; // Here we assume that the interfaces at each side are the same kind
2482  switch (config[donor]->GetKind_TurboInterface(interfaceIndex)) {
2483  case TURBO_INTERFACE_KIND::MIXING_PLANE: {
2484  interface_type = MIXING_PLANE;
2485  auto nVar = solver[donor][INST_0][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
2486  interface[donor][target] = new CMixingPlaneInterface(nVar, 0);
2487  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "using a mixing-plane interface from donor zone " << donor << " to target zone " << target << "." << endl;
2488  break;
2489  }
2490  case TURBO_INTERFACE_KIND::FROZEN_ROTOR: {
2491  auto nVar = solver[donor][INST_0][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnPrimVar();
2492  interface_type = SLIDING_INTERFACE;
2493  interface[donor][target] = new CSlidingInterface(nVar, 0);
2494  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "using a fluid interface interface from donor zone " << donor << " to target zone " << target << "." << endl;
2495  }
2496  }
2497  }
2498  else{
2499  auto nVar = solver[donor][INST_0][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnPrimVar();
2500  interface_type = SLIDING_INTERFACE;
2501  interface[donor][target] = new CSlidingInterface(nVar, 0);
2502  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "sliding interface." << endl;
2503  }
2504  }
2505  else if (heat_donor || heat_target) {
2506  if (heat_donor && heat_target){
2507  interface_type = CONJUGATE_HEAT_SS;
2508 
2509  } else {

2883 void CFluidDriver::StartSolver(){
2884 
2885 #ifdef VTUNEPROF
2886  __itt_resume();
2887 #endif
2888 
2889  /*--- Main external loop of the solver. Within this loop, each iteration ---*/
2890 
2891  if (rank == MASTER_NODE){
2892  cout << endl <<"------------------------------ Begin Solver -----------------------------" << endl;
2893  }
2894 
2895  unsigned long Iter = 0;
2896  while ( Iter < Max_Iter ) {
2897 
2898  /*--- Perform some external iteration preprocessing. ---*/
2899 
2900  Preprocess(Iter);
2901 
2902  /*--- Perform a dynamic mesh update if required. ---*/
2903  /*--- For the Disc.Adj. of a case with (rigidly) moving grid, the appropriate
2904  mesh cordinates are read from the restart files. ---*/
2905  if (!fem_solver &&
2906  !(config_container[ZONE_0]->GetGrid_Movement() && config_container[ZONE_0]->GetDiscrete_Adjoint())) {
2907  DynamicMeshUpdate(Iter);
2908  }
2909 
2910  /*--- Run a single iteration of the problem (fluid, elasticity, heat, ...). ---*/
2911 
2912  Run();
2913 
2914  /*--- Update the solution for dual time stepping strategy ---*/
2915 
2916  Update();
2917 
2918  /*--- Terminate the simulation if only the Jacobian must be computed. ---*/
2919  if (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetJacobian_Spatial_Discretization_Only()) break;
2920 
2921  /*--- Monitor the computations after each iteration. ---*/
2922 
2923  Monitor(Iter);
2924 
2925  /*--- Output the solution in files. ---*/
2926 
2927  Output(Iter);
2928 
2929  /*--- If the convergence criteria has been met, terminate the simulation. ---*/
2930 
2931  if (StopCalc) break;
2932 
2933  Iter++;
2934 
2935  }
2936 #ifdef VTUNEPROF
2937  __itt_pause();
2938 #endif
2939 }

2942 void CFluidDriver::Preprocess(unsigned long Iter) {
2943 
2944  /*--- Set the value of the external iteration and physical time. ---*/
2945 
2946  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
2947  config_container[iZone]->SetInnerIter(Iter);
2948  if (config_container[iZone]->GetTime_Marching() != TIME_MARCHING::STEADY)
2949  config_container[iZone]->SetPhysicalTime(static_cast<su2double>(Iter)*config_container[iZone]->GetDelta_UnstTimeND());
2950  else
2951  config_container[iZone]->SetPhysicalTime(0.0);
2952  }
2953 
2954  /*--- Set the initial condition for EULER/N-S/RANS and for a non FSI simulation ---*/
2955 
2956  if(!fsi) {
2957  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
2958  if (config_container[iZone]->GetFluidProblem()) {
2959  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInst[iZone]; iInst++) {
2960  solver_container[iZone][iInst][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->SetInitialCondition(geometry_container[iZone][INST_0], solver_container[iZone][iInst], config_container[iZone], Iter);
2961  if (config_container[iZone]->GetKind_Species_Model() != SPECIES_MODEL::NONE)
2962  solver_container[iZone][iInst][MESH_0][SPECIES_SOL]->SetInitialCondition(geometry_container[iZone][INST_0], solver_container[iZone][iInst], config_container[iZone], Iter);
2963  }
2964  }
2965  }
2966  }

2969 void CFluidDriver::Run() {
2970 
2971  unsigned short iZone, jZone;
2972  unsigned long IntIter, nIntIter;
2973  bool unsteady;
2974 
2975  /*--- Run a single iteration of a multi-zone problem by looping over all
2976  zones and executing the iterations. Note that data transers between zones
2977  and other intermediate procedures may be required. ---*/
2978 
2979  unsteady = (config_container[MESH_0]->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_1ST) ||
2980  (config_container[MESH_0]->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND);
2981 
2982  /*--- Zone preprocessing ---*/
2983 
2984  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++)
2985  iteration_container[iZone][INST_0]->Preprocess(output_container[iZone], integration_container, geometry_container, solver_container, numerics_container, config_container, surface_movement, grid_movement, FFDBox, iZone, INST_0);
2986 
2987  /*--- Updating zone interface communication patterns,
2988  needed only for unsteady simulation since for steady problems
2989  this is done once in the interpolator_container constructor
2990  at the beginning of the computation ---*/
2991 
2992  if ( unsteady ) {
2993  for (iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
2994  for (jZone = 0; jZone < nZone; jZone++)

3302 void CHBDriver::StabilizeHarmonicBalance() {
3303 
3304  unsigned short i, j, k, iVar, iInst, jInst, iMGlevel;
3305  unsigned short nVar = solver_container[ZONE_0][INST_0][MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->GetnVar();
3306  unsigned long iPoint;
3307  bool adjoint = (config_container[ZONE_0]->GetContinuous_Adjoint());
3308 
3309  /*--- Retrieve values from the config file ---*/
3310  auto *Source = new su2double[nInstHB];
3311  auto *Source_old = new su2double[nInstHB];
3312  su2double Delta;
3313 
3314  auto **Pinv = new su2double*[nInstHB];
3315  auto **P = new su2double*[nInstHB];
3316  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3317  Pinv[iInst] = new su2double[nInstHB];
3318  P[iInst] = new su2double[nInstHB];
3319  }
3320 
3321  /*--- Loop over all grid levels ---*/
3322  for (iMGlevel = 0; iMGlevel <= config_container[ZONE_0]->GetnMGLevels(); iMGlevel++) {
3323 
3324  /*--- Loop over each node in the volume mesh ---*/
3325  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry_container[ZONE_0][INST_0][iMGlevel]->GetnPoint(); iPoint++) {
3326 
3327  /*--- Get time step for current node ---*/
3328  Delta = solver_container[ZONE_0][INST_0][iMGlevel][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetDelta_Time(iPoint);
3329 
3330  /*--- Setup stabilization matrix for this node ---*/
3331  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3332  for (jInst = 0; jInst < nInstHB; jInst++) {
3333  if (jInst == iInst ) {
3334  Pinv[iInst][jInst] = 1.0 + Delta*D[iInst][jInst];
3335  }
3336  else {
3337  Pinv[iInst][jInst] = Delta*D[iInst][jInst];
3338  }
3339  }
3340  }
3341 
3342  /*--- Invert stabilization matrix Pinv with Gauss elimination---*/
3343 
3344  /*-- A temporary matrix to hold the inverse, dynamically allocated ---*/
3345  auto **temp = new su2double*[nInstHB];
3346  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3347  temp[i] = new su2double[2 * nInstHB];
3348  }
3349 
3350  /*--- Copy the desired matrix into the temporary matrix ---*/
3351  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3352  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3353  temp[i][j] = Pinv[i][j];
3354  temp[i][nInstHB + j] = 0;
3355  }
3356  temp[i][nInstHB + i] = 1;
3357  }
3358 
3359  su2double max_val;
3360  unsigned short max_idx;
3361 
3362  /*--- Pivot each column such that the largest number possible divides the other rows ---*/
3363  for (k = 0; k < nInstHB - 1; k++) {
3364  max_idx = k;
3365  max_val = abs(temp[k][k]);
3366  /*--- Find the largest value (pivot) in the column ---*/
3367  for (j = k; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3368  if (abs(temp[j][k]) > max_val) {
3369  max_idx = j;
3370  max_val = abs(temp[j][k]);
3371  }
3372  }
3373 
3374  /*--- Move the row with the highest value up ---*/
3375  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3376  su2double d = temp[k][j];
3377  temp[k][j] = temp[max_idx][j];
3378  temp[max_idx][j] = d;
3379  }
3380  /*--- Subtract the moved row from all other rows ---*/
3381  for (i = k + 1; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3382  su2double c = temp[i][k] / temp[k][k];
3383  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3384  temp[i][j] = temp[i][j] - temp[k][j] * c;
3385  }
3386  }
3387  }
3388 
3389  /*--- Back-substitution ---*/
3390  for (k = nInstHB - 1; k > 0; k--) {
3391  if (temp[k][k] != su2double(0.0)) {
3392  for (int i = k - 1; i > -1; i--) {
3393  su2double c = temp[i][k] / temp[k][k];
3394  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3395  temp[i][j] = temp[i][j] - temp[k][j] * c;
3396  }
3397  }
3398  }
3399  }
3400 
3401  /*--- Normalize the inverse ---*/
3402  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3403  su2double c = temp[i][i];
3404  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3405  temp[i][j + nInstHB] = temp[i][j + nInstHB] / c;
3406  }
3407  }
3408 
3409  /*--- Copy the inverse back to the main program flow ---*/
3410  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3411  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3412  P[i][j] = temp[i][j + nInstHB];
3413  }
3414  }
3415 
3416  /*--- Delete dynamic template ---*/
3417  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3418  delete[] temp[iInst];
3419  }
3420  delete[] temp;
3421 
3422  /*--- Loop through variables to precondition ---*/
3423  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
3424 
3425  /*--- Get current source terms (not yet preconditioned) and zero source array to prepare preconditioning ---*/
3426  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3427  Source_old[iInst] = solver_container[ZONE_0][iInst][iMGlevel][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->GetHarmonicBalance_Source(iPoint, iVar);
3428  Source[iInst] = 0;
3429  }
3430 
3431  /*--- Step through columns ---*/
3432  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++) {
3433  for (jInst = 0; jInst < nInstHB; jInst++) {
3434  Source[iInst] += P[iInst][jInst]*Source_old[jInst];
3435  }
3436 
3437  /*--- Store updated source terms for current node ---*/
3438  if (!adjoint) {
3439  solver_container[ZONE_0][iInst][iMGlevel][FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->SetHarmonicBalance_Source(iPoint, iVar, Source[iInst]);
3440  }
3441  else {
3442  solver_container[ZONE_0][iInst][iMGlevel][ADJFLOW_SOL]->GetNodes()->SetHarmonicBalance_Source(iPoint, iVar, Source[iInst]);
3443  }
3444  }
3445 
3446  }
3447  }
3448  }
3449 
3450  /*--- Deallocate dynamic memory ---*/
3451  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++){
3452  delete [] P[iInst];
3453  delete [] Pinv[iInst];
3454  }
3455  delete [] P;
3456  delete [] Pinv;
3457  delete [] Source;
3458  delete [] Source_old;
3459 
3460 }

3481  Period /= config_container[ZONE_0]->GetTime_Ref();

3486  Omega_HB[iInst] /= config_container[ZONE_0]->GetOmega_Ref(); //TODO: check

3517  temp[i][j] = Einv[i][j];
3518  temp[i][nInstHB + j] = 0;
3519  }
3520  temp[i][nInstHB + i] = 1;
3521  }

3525

3527  for (k = 0; k < nInstHB - 1; k++) {

3530  /*--- Find the largest value (pivot) in the column ---*/
3531  for (j = k; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3532  if (abs(temp[j][k]) > max_val) {
3533  max_idx = j;
3534  max_val = abs(temp[j][k]);
3535  }
3536  }
3537  /*--- Move the row with the highest value up ---*/
3538  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3539  complex<su2double> d = temp[k][j];
3540  temp[k][j] = temp[max_idx][j];
3541  temp[max_idx][j] = d;
3542  }
3543  /*--- Subtract the moved row from all other rows ---*/
3544  for (i = k + 1; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3545  complex<su2double> c = temp[i][k] / temp[k][k];
3546  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3547  temp[i][j] = temp[i][j] - temp[k][j] * c;
3548  }
3549  }
3550  }
3551  /*--- Back-substitution ---*/
3552  for (k = nInstHB - 1; k > 0; k--) {
3553  if (temp[k][k] != complex<su2double>(0.0)) {
3554  for (int i = k - 1; i > -1; i--) {
3555  complex<su2double> c = temp[i][k] / temp[k][k];
3556  for (j = 0; j < (nInstHB * 2); j++) {
3557  temp[i][j] = temp[i][j] - temp[k][j] * c;
3558  }
3559  }
3560  }
3561  }
3562  /*--- Normalize the inverse ---*/
3563  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3564  complex<su2double> c = temp[i][i];
3565  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3566  temp[i][j + nInstHB] = temp[i][j + nInstHB] / c;
3567  }
3568  }
3569  /*--- Copy the inverse back to the main program flow ---*/
3570  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3571  for (j = 0; j < nInstHB; j++) {
3572  E[i][j] = temp[i][j + nInstHB];
3573  }
3574  }
3575  /*--- Delete dynamic template ---*/
3576  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3577  delete[] temp[i];
3578  }
3579  delete[] temp;
3580 
3581 
3582  /*--- Temporary matrix for performing product ---*/
3583  auto **Temp = new complex<su2double>*[nInstHB];
3584 
3585  /*--- Temporary complex HB operator ---*/
3586  auto **Dcpx = new complex<su2double>*[nInstHB];
3587 
3588  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++){
3589  Temp[iInst] = new complex<su2double>[nInstHB];
3590  Dcpx[iInst] = new complex<su2double>[nInstHB];
3591  }
3592 
3593 
3594  /*--- Calculation of the HB operator matrix ---*/
3595  for (int row = 0; row < nInstHB; row++) {
3596  for (int col = 0; col < nInstHB; col++) {
3597  for (int inner = 0; inner < nInstHB; inner++) {
3598  Temp[row][col] += Einv[row][inner] * DD[inner][col];
3599  }
3600  }
3601  }
3602 
3603  unsigned short row, col, inner;
3604 
3605  for (row = 0; row < nInstHB; row++) {
3606  for (col = 0; col < nInstHB; col++) {
3607  for (inner = 0; inner < nInstHB; inner++) {
3608  Dcpx[row][col] += Temp[row][inner] * E[inner][col];
3609  }
3610  }
3611  }
3612 
3613  /*--- Take just the real part of the HB operator matrix ---*/
3614  for (i = 0; i < nInstHB; i++) {
3615  for (k = 0; k < nInstHB; k++) {
3616  D[i][k] = real(Dcpx[i][k]);
3617  }
3618  }
3619 
3620  /*--- Deallocate dynamic memory ---*/
3621  for (iInst = 0; iInst < nInstHB; iInst++){
3622  delete [] E[iInst];
3623  delete [] Einv[iInst];
3624  delete [] DD[iInst];
3625  delete [] Temp[iInst];
3626  delete [] Dcpx[iInst];
3627  }
3628  delete [] E;
3629  delete [] Einv;
3630  delete [] DD;
3631  delete [] Temp;
3632  delete [] Dcpx;
3633  delete [] Omega_HB;
